message.content: A pickup truck is a type of vehicle with an open cargo area in the rear for carrying goods or materials. Its design typically features a front cab for passengers and a separate bed for cargo. Pickup trucks often have four-wheel drive capabilities and are used for a variety of purposes including personal transportation, hauling, and work-related tasks. They can be found in a range of colors and styles, from sleek and modern to rugged and utilitarian. The exterior of a pickup truck may be made of materials such as metal, plastic, or fiberglass. They are commonly used in construction, agriculture, and other industries where heavy lifting and hauling are required.
